{"metadata": {"url": "https://minecraft.fandom.com/wiki/Procedural_animated_texture_generation/Gears", "title": "Procedural_animated_texture_generation/Gears", "time": "17/04/2022 00:53:26"}, "tables": [], "images": [{"src": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/minecraft_gamepedia/images/6/6d/Gear_%28texture%29_JE1.png", "path": "images/img.png", "alt_text": "", "caption": null, "bbox": [443.984375, 597.390625, 120, 120]}, {"src": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/minecraft_gamepedia/images/d/d5/Gear_%28middle_texture%29_JE1.png", "path": "images/img (1).png", "alt_text": "", "caption": null, "bbox": [601.984375, 597.390625, 120, 120]}, {"src": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/minecraft_gamepedia/images/1/1b/Invicon_Gear.gif", "path": "images/img.png", "alt_text": "", "caption": null, "bbox": [443.984375, 966.890625, 120, 120]}, {"src": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/minecraft_gamepedia/images/0/0c/Gear_1_%28texture%29_JE1-a1.gif", "path": "images/img.png", "alt_text": "", "caption": null, "bbox": [601.984375, 966.890625, 120, 120]}], "sprites": [], "texts": [{"text": "Procedural animated texture generation/Gears", "bbox": [202.046875, 317.390625, 593, 90]}, {"text": "Code which generates the frames of the gear texture can be found here.", "bbox": [202.046875, 451.890625, 726, 25]}, {"text": "The animation for gears was generated using two predefined image files - misc/gear.png for the rotating gear and misc/gearmiddle.png for the stationary center.", "bbox": [202.046875, 500.390625, 726, 49]}, {"text": "misc/gear.png\nmisc/gearmiddle.png", "bbox": [238.046875, 573.390625, 690, 181]}, {"text": "misc/gear.png", "bbox": [426.484375, 733.390625, 155, 19]}, {"text": "misc/gearmiddle.png", "bbox": [584.484375, 733.390625, 155, 19]}, {"text": "The animation, updated every game tick,[1] is rendered as a 16x16 texture like most other blocks. The resulting gear has 18.75 RPM.[1]", "bbox": [202.046875, 772.390625, 726, 49]}, {"text": "There are two different animations used for gears - one for clockwise rotation, and another for anticlockwise rotation, to allow for logical meshing. These are generated effectively identically, with the only difference being the direction of rotation; both start on the same frame, but cycle through them in the opposite direction.[1]", "bbox": [202.046875, 845.390625, 726, 73]}, {"text": "Clockwise rotation\nAnticlockwise rotation", "bbox": [238.046875, 942.890625, 690, 180]}, {"text": "Clockwise rotation", "bbox": [426.484375, 1102.890625, 155, 18]}, {"text": "Anticlockwise rotation", "bbox": [584.484375, 1102.890625, 155, 18]}, {"text": "https://github.com/NeRdTheNed/MC-TextureGen/releases/tag/v1.2.0", "bbox": [275.046875, 1143.890625, 457, 17]}]}